      "Microstructure_Info": {
        "Microstructure_Text": {
          "original": "The as-printed alloy has a single-phase FCC structure with conventional polycrystalline morphology and an average grain size of 29.7 μm. Cellular structures with an average size of ~400 nm prevail inside the grains, and cellular walls are decorated with a high density of dislocations. Ti enrichment is observed at cellular boundaries, with slight depletion of Co and Cr. Average KAM value is 0.85°.",
          "simplified": "Single-phase FCC, grain size 29.7 μm, cellular substructure (~400 nm) with Ti-rich boundaries and high dislocation density."
        },
