      "Process_Info": {
        "Process_Category": "Additive Manufacturing + Heat Treatment",
        "Process_Text": {
          "original": "The gas-atomized Al5Ti5 HEA powders with an average particle size of 36.36 μm were used to fabricate Al5Ti5 bulk specimens. The SLM was performed using a laser powder-bed-fusion (LPBF) printer (SLM-100, Guangdong Hanbang) under an argon atmosphere with optimized printing parameters (laser power: 175 W, scan speed: 1000 mm/s, layer thickness: 30 μm, hatching space: 80 μm). Subsequently, the as-printed specimen was aged at 700 °C for 4 h to introduce the second reinforced phase, i.e., the L1₂ nanoprecipitates. The aging heat treatment ended with air cooling.",
          "simplified": "SLM as described, followed by aging at 700 °C for 4 h and air cooling."
        },
        "Equipment": "SLM-100 (Guangdong Hanbang) laser powder-bed-fusion printer",
        "Key_Params": {
          "Laser_Power_W": 175,
          "Scanning_Speed_mm_s": 1000,
          "Layer_Thickness_um": 30,
          "Hatch_Spacing_um": 80,
          "Protective_Atmosphere": "Argon",
          "Powder_Size_avg_um": 36.36,
          "Aging_Temperature_K": 973.15,
          "Aging_Time_h": 4,
          "Cooling_Medium": "Air"
        }
      },
      "Microstructure_Info": {
        "Microstructure_Text": {
          "original": "The aged alloy exhibits a dual-phase structure (FCC + L1₂) with a refined average grain size of 9.2 μm. Discontinuous precipitation of lamellar L1₂ nanorods occurs, and cellular structures are partially retained in the continuous precipitation region. L1₂ precipitates are enriched in Ni, Al, Ti and depleted in Co and Cr; the volume fraction of L1₂ is ~37%. The lattice mismatch between FCC matrix and L1₂ is 0.28%. Average KAM value reduces to 0.67°.",
          "simplified": "FCC + L1₂ dual-phase, grain size 9.2 μm, ~37 vol% lamellar L1₂ nanorods coherent with matrix."
